<h3><a id="execs" name="execs"></a>4.
Exercises</h3>
<blockquote> <a id="ex1" name="ex1"></a>Create
a directory named "<span style="font-weight: bold;">project2</span>"
under your web server's document root directory on your hard drive.
Place all HTML files and PHP scripts for this project in this new
directory. <br>
  <br>
  <span style="font-weight: bold;">Note:</span>
If you are working on an MATC lab computer, always save a copy of this
directory and all the files in it to either the class server, a USB
thumb drive, a floppy disk or similar media, at the end of each work
session. Otherwise your work will be lost!
  <h4>Exercise 1</h4>
  <p>Create a PHP include file
named <span style="font-weight: bold;">db.inc</span> <span
 style="font-weight: bold;"></span>that
contains the following:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>Variable assignments
for connecting to your account, and the <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">winestore</span>
database on the class MySQL server, 198.150.221.235. </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>The <span style="font-weight: bold;">showerror( )</span>
function as used in Chapter 6 of the text.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p>Hint: See Example 6-7 in
Chapter 6<br>
  </p>
  <h4>Exercise 2</h4>
  <p>Write a PHP
script named "<span style="font-weight: bold;">display_wines.php</span>"
that queries the <span style="font-weight: bold;">wine</span>
table of the winestore database.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Use the<span style="font-weight: bold;"> require</span>
directive to include the db.inc file in your script</li>
    <li>Connect to the class MySQL server using the function <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">mysql_connect( )</span> . The script should
terminate with an error message if it fails to connect.<br>
    </li>
    <li>Select the winestore database using the function <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">mysql_select_db( )</span> . The script
should use the showerror() function to terminate itself if database
selection fails. <br>
    </li>
    <li>Run an SQL query to select all rows from the wine table using
the function <span style="font-weight: bold;">mysql_query( )</span> .
The script should use the showerror() function to terminate itself if
the query fails. </li>
    <li> Use a <span style="font-weight: bold;">while</span> loop and
the function <span style="font-weight: bold;">mysql_fetch_array( )</span>
to retrieve the result set one row at a time. Your script should print
appropriate column headings for each column in the table.<br>
    </li>
    <li>Print the column values for all rows in the table using HTML
tags to format your output as an HTML table. <br>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <li>
    <p>Note: Your script <span style="font-weight: bold;">must </span>use
variables defined in the db.inc file rather than literals for
connection to the MySQL server and selection of the database! </p>
